title: Trump-like libertarian Javier Milei set to win Argentina’s presidency
description: Javier Milei, a former television pundit with no governing experience, rode a wave of voter rage to win Argentina’s presidency, with his main rival conceding defeat even before official results were out.

title: Israel, Hamas and U.S. nearing deal on hostage release, senior officials say
description: The U.S. deputy national security adviser, Israel’s ambassador to Washington and Qatar’s prime minister all independently said an agreement to release some hostages and pause fighting was close.

title: A midnight trip into northern Gaza reveals a shattered warscape
description: The Post entered Gaza with a small group of journalists, escorted by the Israeli military. Israel’s control of the north appears firm; the destruction total.

title: Medical provider vying for border contract faces scrutiny after girl’s death
description: A medical services company whose quality of care is being investigated after the death of a girl in U.S. border custody is a finalist for a new $1.5 billion contract

title: A split emerges as Biden struggles to deter attacks on U.S. troops
description: Frustration is building within the Defense Department, officials say, over the surge in Iranian proxy attacks on American military positions.

title: Trapped for 12 hours under rubble in Gaza: One woman’s story
description: Palestinian officials say thousands are missing and could be trapped under collapsed buildings.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Deal near on 5-day pause in fighting; WHO calls al-Shifa a ‘death zone’
description: Israel and Hamas are close to agreeing to a U.S.-brokered deal on a pause in exchange for the release of dozens of hostages in Gaza, people familiar with the terms told The Post.

title: Creeping escalation along Israel-Lebanon border brings risk of bigger war
description: What began as tit-for-tat retaliation between Hezbollah and Israel on the Lebanese border has blurred into a steady conflict, sparking fears of all-out war.
